“Agency” has the meaning assigned to the word in the Act;
“bulk toll discount” means a wholesale price discount applicable
to a road user who purchases tolls in bulk;
“concession agreement” means the agreement entered into
between the concessionaire and the contracting authority
for the design, financing, construction, operation,
maintenance and transfer of the Sakania Border Post
infrastructure, the Ndola-Mufulira Road and the access road
to the Sakania Border Post on the Copperbelt Province of
Zambia;
“contracting authority” means the Agency, the Ministry
responsible for Finance and National Planning and the
Ministry responsible for Commerce, Trade and Industry;
“concessionaire” means Jaswin Ports Limited;
“frequent road user” means a Zambian registered vehicle that
uses a toll road for a specified minimum number of times in
a specified period as determined by the concessionaire;
Copies of this Statutory Instrument can be obtained from the Government Printer,
P.O. Box 30136, 10101 Lusaka. Price K8.00 each.
96 Statutory Instruments 13h February, 2026
“frequent road user discount” means a toll tariff granted to a
regular road user at a designated inland toll point for a
specified period;
“independent consultant” means a person appointed as an
independent consultant in accordance with the concession
agreement;
“local user” means a road user driving a Zambian registered
vehicle domiciled within a ten kilometre radius of an inland
toll point, excluding a port of entry;
“local user discount” means a toll levied on a local user to a
specific toll point for a specified period of time;
“partial practical completion certificate” means a certificate
issued by an independent consultant or the contracting
authority to the concessionaire when the tests conducted
on the Ndola-Sakania Road and the Tom Mtine Toll Plaza
are verified and the Ndola-Sakania Road and Tom Mtine
Toll Plaza are confirmed to be safe and reliable for the
commencement of commercial operations;
“toll” has the meaning assigned to the word in the Act;
“toll point” means a point designated for the collection of tolls
under regulation 3; and
“toll road” has the meaning assigned to the words in the Act.
